content.detailedDescription: My friends and i were outside since it was nice out. there were seven of us. one of the little kids made two of my friends mad so i suggested we lay down in my friends driveway and look at the stars. we were talking when i noticed the light from a star was blocked out for a moment. i had a double-take and when i looked again, i saw a triangular shaped craft with four orange lights. three of these four lights were located near the tips of the craft while the fourth was in the middle. i was in shock. i live in a busy area and my father and i are involved with astronomy and own two telescopes. we both look at the stars all of the time and live near an airport,so we have a very clear idea of what a plane looks like at night. this object wasn't hard to see or obscured by clouds, and i could clearly make out the shape and lights on it. when i saw it, i immediately stood up and shouted to everyone and pointed out the object. one of my friends saw it and kept his eye on it. the object was relatively slow and very low, moving northwest. this friend always blew off anything about ufo's and thought the whole idea of it was bogus. that is no longer the case. two other people caught a glance of it, but saw it just before it escaped our point of view. of course, no one else saw it and when we talk about it they just belittle us. but my friend and i know what we saw.
content.summary: A triangular shaped craft with four orange lights passed silently over my neighborhood. it was very clear.

content.detailedDescription: My sister, and brother-in-law and i, and our 5 children were taking the "back way" home from an all day trip to king's island...Which is located in cincinnati, ohio...It was getting late at night..My sister and i had the 2 older kids, and the youngest child in the mini-van with us..My brother-in-law had the 2 middle kids with him, and, he was traveling ahead of us going north on pennville road....My sister and i were talking when, suddenly, to our right, we saw this huge greyish colored "disc" pop down under the clouds....We both were shocked by it! my sister and i, at the same time, exclaimed, "did you see that!!!!!?" as fast as it descended (which only took less than a few seconds..) it immediately shot straight back up into the sky!!...I exclaimed that it had to be a ufo, and my sister gave me the "evil eye" and said,"no, it was just a shooting star.." i told her she was crazy, and, to avoid an argument, i just let it drop....It was pretty dark that night, out in the middle of the country..There were no street lights...The thing had to have been huge, because it looked to be bigger than her mini-van..It all happened in a split second...I have seen shooting stars..They look bright, and appear to be somewhat small...Also, they usually don't shoot right back straight up into the sky!!! the disc had a "glowing" characteristic about it..Not bright, but, bright enough for us to see it...Another strange thing that happened,was that we were headed to a "t" in the road..It intersects with u.S.40....As we got to the intersection, an unmarked, white police car, with blacked out wheels came squealing off of u.S. 40 headed south...Keep in mind that we were out in the "boonies" at about 10:30-11:00 at night...We didn't pass any accidents, and didn't see anything suspicious (except for the disc...)  there wasn't any other traffic on the road that night...He could have been responding to an emergency, but, the coincidence really unnerved me....It all happened so fast! my sister and i just let it drop...We didn't mention it again! as large as the disc appeared to be, i would approximate it to have been probably about 1-2 miles away from us....I have never seen anything like it before, or since..
content.summary: Large, luminescent, grey, looked like the "old-fashioned" flying discs from the 1950's movies

content.detailedDescription:
Myself and 2 fishing friend have camped for 10 years on an island on a lake in mid-maine for the last 15 years. always at the end of september when the island is empty. we take a boat ride at sunset to have a few beers and enjoy the view. on our way back in the dark we decided to circle the island. there is a campsite at the east end of the island which i had viisted before. it is wide open and grass covered. blue orbs the size of basket ball were jumping and rushing through around the site.We witnessed this for 10 minutes till we passed a point.My friend driving the boat was to spooked to stop.

the next day we hiked around the island to the site. the grass was 4 inchs high. but not a blade was laided done. no foot prints. nothing.

content.detailedDescription:
I was driving southbound on i-15 at approximately 6 pm pst, 3/24/2010. i had just left the riverside area. i noticed a object in the air over an open field on the northbound side of the interstate. at first glance, i thought the object was a helicopter. as my car approached the object, however, i discerned a rectangular shape and noticed that the object was stationary in the air. i estimate the object was roughly 500 - 700 feet above the ground, and approximately 60 - 90 feet long on the side facing me. it was generally light gray in color...Nearly the ambient color of the sky at that time. it had lights along the exterior edges, and a flashing red light on one end.

my wife was in the car with me at the time. she thought the object might be a helicopter (she made that observation after we had passed the object and it was no longer visible). i had suspected this myself when i first noticed the object in the distance, but changed my mind as we passed it by and i was able to view it more closely. she did not view the object as we passed by. we were traveling at approximately 70 mph. 

due to the traffic conditions at the time, i was not able to immediately pull over in order to observe this object more closely. i was going to do so approximately a quarter-mile down the highway...But when i looked in the rear-view mirror at where the object should be, it was gone. 

i estimate 1 minute 15 seconds elapsed between the moment when i first noticed the object, to when i was able to discern that it wasn't a helicopter. i searched for a place to pull over (paying close attention to traffic), looked in the rear-view mirror, and noticed the object was gone.

this incident strikes me as unusual as i am typically able to discern types of aircraft under most visibility conditions (i was in the military and so am accustomed to viewing all kinds of helicopters). this one was highly unusual due to the rectangular shape of the object. it stuck in mind, because this is the first time i have ever witnessed what amounts to a ufo in my life.
content.summary: Hovering rectangular object, surrounded by lights with one red flashing light

content.detailedDescription: I was leaving my friends house and she was walking me out. we stopped and she was talking to another friend of ours that was up on a balcony. i was looking up at the moon and stars, it was a very clear night. i saw the object and thought, what is that? at first i thought could it be a bird but within a second i knew it was not a bird because of it's perfect triangle shape and there was no flapping of wings. also it flew in a strait line, and very smoothy. then i thought, is it some kind of crazy looking plane?, but i noted that there were no lights on it, and again that triangle shape was not like a plane. then i thought oh my gosh i'm actually seeing a ufo. i then pointed and said to my friend "do you see that?" but i knew it was about to be out of sight, and it was, that was when i noticed how fast it was moving because a plane would not be out of sight so fast, and because there was no sound for me of my friends to hear. i told them what i saw. and that's it.
content.summary: Triangle, gray, no lights (on at least),  no sound, flying fast and very smoothly, surface seemed not totally smooth.

content.detailedDescription:
I was driving to my nightshift job when an object caught my eye,it was at distance at first maybe 500 to 800 feet away but only 300 - 500 feet in the air.I thought it was a street light at first but it was completely the wrong place, it was its position over the houses that made me give it a second look.It was glowing orange/red about the size of a 5 pence piece and didn't move just stayed motionless above the houses at the side of the road, as i drove past i slowed right down but couldn't stop as i was on a main road.I remember thinking at the time it was a really random thing to see i almost didnt believe i was seeing it.I had never mentioned this to anyone, however two good friend of mine were waiting to for me to pick them up about 3 weeks ago and without any prior knowledge described exactly the same thing i had seen months before.Now last weekend a neighbour of another friend asked if we had seen the sun looking object on the horizon the previous night.
now these people have met maybe a handful of times and there is no way they could colaberate the story without meeting first and i hadn't told them of my incident until the spoke of what they had seen.

content.detailedDescription:
I stepped out back back to have a cigarette and it was before daylight savings, so it was very dark still at 8pm. from my yard i can see many flights preparing to get into their landing paths as ohare is east of me, but this was different. looking east from carol stream to what appeared to be in the direction of ohare there was a cluster of bright lights in a horizontal line that remained stationary, bright and flashed red and orange at this point (almost spinning) some moving in and out of vision and some staying, but the ones that disappeared returned to sight after just seconds. 

for the most part they stayed in a horizontal line or moved to a semi circle formation with some disappearing and returning and some disappearing all togehter. but there are consistantly 2-3 bright, glowing pulsating orbs that just don't move at all.  
assuming they were planes, i continued to watch them to make sure they were moving lower to land, but it didn't happen. the distance from the ground wasn't changing.

i grabbed my camera, jumped in my car and drove about 2 miles east to the mall parking lot where the lights were still there pulsating and moving in and out of the picture/videos i've included.

still not convinced, or maybe just freaked at this point and amazed that no one else was seeing what i saw, i drove another approx 2 miles east to a parking lot that's on a hill where i was able to get additoinal shots of the view where these orbs were still visible.


being visible from my back yard that night, i've checked every night since at various time to see if it was possibly planes in a holding pattern, but it's not happened since. i hadn't really noticed them spinning/pulsating from the naked eye, but noticed when i viewed the videos.

the first video was from the mall parking lot (2 miles east of my house) adn the second video was from the hilled parking lot (4 miles east of my house).  i used just a cannon digital camera and have litle skill and apparently shakey hands, but tried to zoom in/out so you can see the landscape.  i also have some pictures as well. 

keep in mind the line of bright white lights in the video under the white and orange pulsating orbs are actually street lights.  keep you eye right above them to see the pulsating orbs moving in and out of view (video 2)

the picture quality is not very good, but zoom in on the lone orange orb high above the street lights. maybe a plane,but in line with vid 2 and the orbs.

the sky was clear and it was approx 40 degrees.  i'm sorry for the quality of the videos, but it was the best i could so at the time.
content.summary: Stationary and pulsating orange orbs seen from chicago suburb.

content.detailedDescription:
About a month or two ago while  driving home from st louis ,i noticed bright lights from what i thought was an airplane. i have never seen bright lights on an airplane like this and i lived in that area my whole life. the lights turned and moved slowly away from me and i assumed it was just an aitplane or helicopter. 

last night while driving home i saw the exact same bright lights, but this time it was much closer to the ground and stationary. as i approached this object i was waiting for the moment when i could tell myself "its just a plane". i didn't get to do that. it was some sort of space ship or unknown something! looked like it was not of this world. it resembled a claw, kinda like the ones you use to win prizes at carnivals. except it had four "claws". neon blue lights at the tip of each one, they were hard to see until i got close, the shape of the claws were seemingly designed to hide the light. once i drove under the craft i noticed it had four white lights under the very center of the craft. these were not the same bright lights that i noticed from far away,those were like headlights and there were five of those, small outside lights medium sized towards the center and one big light in the center. the four white lights under the center had a small red light directly in the center of them, this was also the center of the bottom of the craft. once i passed the craft, i could not see it any more when i looked back.


one last thing is the physical part of this craft was blacker than the night sky. i got a real good look at this thing and will attach a sketch as soon as possible.
